(42, 9, 33, 43, 14, 8, 8, 'it is good for us to be here', 'Desire for Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the desire of the disciples to encounter the divine. Peter''s request to build tabernacles reflects a longing for a tangible presence of God, similar to Philip''s request to see the Father.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 33, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'good for us to be here', 'Light and Glory Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation. In Luke, Peter''s desire to dwell in the presence of Jesus, Moses, and Elias reflects a yearning for the glory of God, which is further emphasized in 2 Corinthians as the light of God''s glory shining in our hearts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 34, 2, 40, 34, 38, 'a cloud, and overshadowed them', 'Divine Presence in Cloud', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s presence represented by a cloud. Both passages describe a cloud that signifies divine glory and authority, instilling fear and reverence in those who encounter it.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 34, 40, 17, 5, 7, 'a cloud, and overshadowed them', 'Divine Revelation in Clouds', 'Both passages emphasize a cloud overshadowing the disciples, indicating a divine presence. Additionally, Matthew includes a voice from the cloud affirming Jesus as God''s Son, which enhances the significance of the moment.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 34, 2, 14, 19, 20, 'a cloud, and overshadowed them', 'Connection of Divine Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine presence represented by a cloud. Both passages describe a cloud that signifies God''s intervention and guidance, instilling fear and awe in those who encounter it.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 34, 7, 6, 22, 22, 'feared as they entered into the cloud', 'Divine Encounter and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize a profound encounter with the divine that induces fear. In Luke, the overshadowing cloud signifies God''s presence, while Gideon''s realization of seeing an angel evokes a similar fear.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
