(42, 9, 34, 19, 18, 9, 11, 'a cloud, and overshadowed them', 'Divine Presence in Clouds', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of God enveloped in clouds, evoking fear and awe. The cloud in Luke signifies divine revelation, while Psalms describes Godâ€™s majesty and mystery associated with darkness and clouds.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 34, 23, 19, 1, 1, 'a cloud, and overshadowed them', 'Divine Presence in Clouds', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of God associated with clouds. In Luke, the cloud overshadows the disciples, while in Isaiah, the Lord rides upon a swift cloud, indicating divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
