(42, 9, 35, 44, 3, 22, 23, 'hear him', 'Hearing the Prophet', 'This connection highlights the importance of hearing God''s chosen messenger. Both passages emphasize the necessity of listening to the one whom God has appointed, linking Jesus as the beloved Son to the prophet foretold by Moses.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 35, 5, 18, 18, 19, 'This is my beloved Son: hear him.', 'Divine Authority of the Prophet', 'This connection highlights the divine endorsement of Jesus as God''s Son in Luke, paralleling the prophetic authority given in Deuteronomy. Both passages emphasize the importance of heeding the words of God''s chosen messenger.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 35, 58, 3, 15, 15, 'hear him', 'Hearing the Voice of God', 'This connection highlights the importance of hearing God''s voice in both passages. Luke emphasizes the command to ''hear him,'' while Hebrews warns against hardening hearts when hearing His voice.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 35, 58, 5, 9, 9, 'hear him', 'Connection of Obedience to the Son', 'This connection highlights the call to ''hear him'' in Luke, which implies obedience to Jesus. Hebrews emphasizes that eternal salvation is for those who obey him, linking the necessity of listening to and following the Son.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 35, 23, 42, 1, 1, 'my beloved Son', 'Divine Affirmation of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the divine endorsement of Jesus as God''s beloved Son in Luke, paralleling the description of God''s chosen servant in Isaiah. Both passages emphasize the theme of divine delight and support for the one who will fulfill God''s purpose.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 36, 40, 17, 9, 9, 'told no man in those days any of those things which they had seen', 'Silence After the Vision', 'Both passages emphasize the command to keep the vision secret. In Luke, they ''told no man'' about what they had seen, while in Matthew, Jesus instructs them to ''Tell the vision to no man.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 36, 41, 9, 9, 10, 'told no man in those days any of those things which they had seen', 'Silence After the Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the command to remain silent about the vision they witnessed. This connection highlights the importance of withholding information until a future event, specifically the resurrection of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 36, 21, 3, 7, 7, 'kept it close, and told no man', 'Silence and Speaking', 'This connection highlights the theme of silence and the appropriate timing for speaking. In Luke 9:36, the disciples kept silent about their experience, while Ecclesiastes 3:7 emphasizes a time to keep silence and a time to speak.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 36, 41, 9, 6, 6, NULL, 'Fear and Silence in Transfiguration', 'Both passages emphasize the fear experienced by the disciples during the Transfiguration event. In Luke, the aftermath leads to silence about the experience, while Mark highlights their fear as a reason for not knowing what to say.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 37, 40, 17, 14, 20, 'much people met him', 'Healing and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the arrival of Jesus to a multitude and the subsequent healing of a boy. The mention of the crowd in Luke sets the stage for the father''s plea for help in Matthew, highlighting themes of faith and healing.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 37, 41, 9, 14, 29, 'much people met him', 'Jesus'' Return to the Crowd', 'Both passages emphasize the moment when Jesus returns to a crowd after an event on a mountain. The presence of the multitude in both accounts highlights the immediate need for Jesus'' healing power upon his descent.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 38, 38, 12, 10, 10, 'mine only child', 'Connection of Mourning for Sons', 'Both passages emphasize the deep sorrow associated with an only son. The mourning described in Zechariah parallels the father''s plea for his only child in Luke, highlighting the emotional weight of loss.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 38, 43, 4, 47, 47, 'my son: for he is mine only child', 'Connection of Parental Concern', 'Both passages emphasize a father''s desperate plea for his son. In Luke, the father seeks help for his only child, while in John, the father begs Jesus to heal his son who is near death.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 38, 40, 15, 22, 22, NULL, 'Parental Pleas for Healing', 'Both passages emphasize a parent''s desperate plea for help regarding their afflicted child. The father in Luke seeks healing for his only son, while the Canaanite woman in Matthew seeks mercy for her daughter.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
